<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815B.20/82: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General in Martinique (<persName type="from">Malige</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort-de-France</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-13T10:00:00-04:00">July 13,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 12:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>263. From Reber. My 260, July 10.<note n="6" xml:id="d635fn6">Not
                                printed.</note> Robert has been informed by his Government that the
                            agreement giving United States Consul at Casablanca permanent control of
                            the parts taken from the ships <pb facs="0648" n="642" xml:id="pg_642"/>
                            and planes here will be carried out and that new instructions have been
                            sent to Casablanca so that there will be no further misunderstanding.
                            [Reber.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Malige</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>